ENTRY            A0643   20260204   20260401   20260401       A131
SUBENT        A0643001   20260204   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                 10         23
TITLE      Yield of 123I in 124Xe irradiation with protons in
           the 16-21.5 MeV energy range
AUTHOR     (N.A.Konyakhin,V.N.Mironov,N.N.Krasnov,P.P.Dmitriev,
           V.P.Lapin,M.V.Panarin)
INSTITUTE  (4RUSFEI)
REFERENCE  (J,SJA,67,639,1989) Translation of
           (J,AE,67,129,1989) In Russian
FACILITY   (CYCLO,4RUSFEI)
SAMPLE     (54-XE-124,ENR=0.999) Six thin gaseous targets
            [16.6 mg/cm2] enriched to 99.9% in 124-Xe were
           irradiated simultaneously.
MONITOR    (29-CU-65(P,N)30-ZN-65,,SIG)
DETECTOR   (GELI) Ge (Li)-detector and a multichannel analyzer
METHOD     (STTA,ACTIV)
           (GSPEC) Activity of 123I was measured at 16, 42, and
           64 hours after irradiation.
           (EXTB) Beam current was 0.5 muA.
HISTORY    (19990629C) By F.C.
           (20000717U) Last checking has been done.
           (20000717A) Date is corrected
           (20180126A) SD: REACTION code was updated according to
           MEMO CP-D/933rev. in Subent 002. BIB was updated.
           (20260204U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              23
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           26
SUBENT        A0643002   20260204   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                  6         15
REACTION   (54-XE-124(P,X)53-I-123,CUM,TTY,,PHY)
COMMENT    - By compiler - Main reaction channel is
           54-Xe-124(P,2N)55-Cs-123.
           -By author - 121Te activity was observed. The activity
           is product of radioactive decay of 121I produced by
           124Xe(P,A)121I reaction.
           *By compiler* The angle between X and Y axes
           on this figure is not equal to 90 degr.
            This deviation is -2.62E-02 radians.
DECAY-DATA (53-I-123,,DG,153.97,0.834)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about partial uncertainties.
STATUS     (CURVE,,N.A.Konyakhin+,J,SJA,67,639,1989) fig.4
HISTORY    (20180126A) SD: SF3=2P ->X, SF8=DT -> PHY, SF9=EXP
           deleted from REACTION code. ERR-T -> DATA-ERR.
           (20260204U) SD: STATUS updated.
ENDBIB              15
COMMON               2          3
EN-ERR-DIG DATA-ERR
MEV        PER-CENT
       0.03        10.
ENDCOMMON            3
DATA                 2          6
EN         DATA
MEV        MUCI/MUAHR
      16.21       0.21
      17.08        0.8
      17.94        2.2
      18.83        4.2
      19.83        7.2
      21.56        13.
ENDDATA              8
ENDSUBENT           32
ENDENTRY             2
